                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16243402" author="dsmiley" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 05:24:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch that fixes the problem.  I decided to move the &quot;path&quot; manipulation out of extractRemotePath so that we have the nice property that it&apos;s only ever updated from init() without exceptions... plus it makes it easier to call by V2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no explicit test admittedly :-/   except that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11542&quot; title=&quot;Add URP to route time partitioned collections&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-11542&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-11542&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; triggers this bug and it now works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=noble.paul&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;noble.paul&quot;&gt;noble.paul&lt;/a&gt; could you please take a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16243417" author="noble.paul" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 05:50:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dsmiley&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dsmiley&quot;&gt;dsmiley&lt;/a&gt; . I dunno how this slipped through the cracks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16243470" author="shalinmangar" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 07:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sounds very similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11130&quot; title=&quot;V2Request in SolrJ should return the correct collection name so that the request is forwarded to the   correct node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-11130&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-11130&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which was supposed to have been fixed for 7.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
